+# D.U.H. Documentation Set
+
+- [Architecture](./ARCHITECTURE.md)
+
+  `ARCHITECTURE.md` explains how the CLI, session builder, kernel, ports, adapters, tools, and security layers fit together. It follows a request from parser entry to rendered output, then calls out the real extension seams for providers, tools, and slash commands.
+
+- [Tutorial](./TUTORIAL.md)
+
+  `TUTORIAL.md` is a source-accurate, runnable path from installation to a working custom tool. It covers Python 3.12 setup, stub-mode CLI validation, runtime tool registration with `NativeExecutor`, approval-policy behavior, and the files you would touch to promote the demo into a built-in tool.
+
+- [API Reference](./API.md)
+
+  `API.md` is the module-by-module reference for the public surface of `duh/kernel/` and `duh/ports/`. It records source-derived signatures, summarizes purpose and return behavior, and lists the public methods that make up the kernel’s practical programming interface.

